<h1>How many names can you remember?</h1>
<div id="fb-loading">
  <p>Hi there, we're loading the Facebook interface now.  Please give us a sec while it loads.</p>
  <p><em>(If nothing happens, try reloading or just come back another time - the site might be down)</em></p>
</div>
<div id="fb-root"></div>
<script>
  window.fbAsyncInit = function() {
    FB.init({appId: '<%= Settings.fb_app_id %>', status: true, cookie: true,
             xfbml: true});
    initApp();
  };
  (function() {
    var e = document.createElement('script'); e.async = true;
    e.src = document.location.protocol +
      '//connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js';
    document.getElementById('fb-root').appendChild(e);
  }());
</script>
<div id="fb-login" style="display: none;">
<p>Hi there!  This is just a quick side project I made to play around with the Facebook API and test my knowledge of the names of my Facebook friends :P.</p>
<p>
<em>None of your Facebook data will be stored (in fact, no data even goes to the server)</em>
</p>
<fb:login-button show-faces="true" width="200" max-rows="1" perms="friends_photo_video_tags">Login with Facebook</fb:login-button>
</div>
<div id="namethat-loading" style="display: none">
  <%= image_tag "loading.gif", :id => "loading-image" %>
</div>
<div id="namethat-app" style="display: none">
  <div class="app-instructions">
    <p>Just type the first name (last name if you're feeling daring) of the person you see in the photo.</p>
    <div class="tips-box">
      <p><strong>Picture sucks?</strong> Click the "Give me another photo" or type ! in the textbox.</p>
      <p><strong>Don't know which person?</strong> Click "Show Photo Tag" or type # in the textbox.</p>
      <p><strong>Still doesn't work?</strong> Click "Skip Question" or type &gt; in the textbox.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="app-score">
    <strong>Your score: </strong><span id="score"></span>
  </div>
  <div class="app-input">
    <input id="answer" name="answer" autocomplete="off" type="text" />
    <input id="check" value="Check" type="button" />
  </div>
  <div class="app-links">
    <a href="#" id="next-photo">Give me another photo</a> |
    <a href="#" id="tag-photo">Show Photo Tag</a> |
    <a href="#" id="skip-question">Skip Question</a>
  </div>
  <div class="app-status">
    <span id="status" style="opacity: 0">A</span>
  </div>
  <img id="friend-photo" />
  <%= image_tag "circle.png", :id => "circle-image" %>
  <br />
  <fb:like href="http://namethat.ktam.org/" send="true" width="450" show_faces="true" font="verdana"></fb:like>
</div>
